OL,6,F"We know that Shami was probably
OL,7,Fassociating with some members of the
OL,8,Fcriminal fraternity. I don't think he
OL,9,Fwas involved in organised crime, but I
OL,10,Fdo think he got himself involved with
OL,11,Fpeople who were and probably found
OL,12,Fhimself out of his depth. This is why
OL,13,FI think he was killed.
OL,15,F"We know that loyalties change over
OL,16,Fthe years, and this is exactly what we
OL,17,Fare relying on. We are hoping that
OL,18,Fpeople that felt they were not able to
OL,19,Fspeak out all that time ago will feel
OL,20,Fdifferently now and feel able to come
OL,21,Fforward.
